Interface InteractionRule

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    InteractionRuleL2, InteractionRuleL3
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AffectsRule, ComponentRule, ComponentRule, ConsecutiveCatalysisRule, ConsecutiveCatalysisRule, ControlRule, ControlRule, ControlsTogetherRule, ControlsTogetherRule, ExpressionRule, InteractionRuleL2Adaptor, InteractionRuleL3Adaptor, ParticipatesRule, ParticipatesRule

    public interface InteractionRule
    This interface defines a rule which can be run on BioPAX model to derive simple interactions. All new rules should implement this interface. User: demir Date: Dec 28, 2007 Time: 3:49:46 PM

      • inferInteractions

        void inferInteractions(InteractionSet set,
                       BioPAXElement entity,
                       Model model)
        This method populates the interactionSet with simple interactions that can be derived from the model based on this rule.
        Parameters:
        set - to be populated
        entity - this must be a physicalEntity for L2, and PhysicalEntity for L3
        model - BioPAX model

      • initOptions

        void initOptions(Map options)
        Uses the parameter map as options for the rule. Each rule defines its possible keys for the options map. Values are always Boolean.
        Parameters:
        options - options map
